reg_info.full_title: R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 624: STOP SIGNS IN TERRITORY WITHOUT MUNICIPAL ORGANIZATION
reg_info.reg_name_text: STOP SIGNS IN TERRITORY WITHOUT MUNICIPAL ORGANIZATION
reg_info.act_under: Highway Traffic Act   Code de la route

content.content: 1. The intersections on highways in territory without municipal organization that are described in paragraph 1 of each Schedule are designated as intersections at which stop signs shall be erected to face traffic travelling in the direction referred to in paragraph 2 of each Schedule.  R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 624, s. 1.
content.raw_html: 1. The intersections on highways in territory without municipal organization that are described in paragraph 1 of each Schedule are designated as intersections at which stop signs shall be erected to face traffic travelling in the direction referred to in paragraph 2 of each Schedule.  R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 624, s. 1.

content.content: 2. Where a highway is referred to in a Schedule by a number or name, the reference is to that part of the highway in a territory without municipal organization that is known thereby.  R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 624, s. 2. Schedule 1
